Package: data.table.threads
Title: Analyze multithreading performance for data.table functions
Version: 0.1.1
Author: Anirban Chetia <Anirban.Chetia@nau.edu> 
Description: Assists in finding the optimal thread count for different data.table
             routines that are parallelizable by providing a function that
             benchmarks the runtime for operations using each routine across 
             varying number of threads (based on your system), and then computes
             the speedup for generating plots that delineate the performance 
             per function for each thread count and highlight the ones with
             maximum gain.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
URL: https://github.com/Anirban166/data.table.threads
Imports: ggplot2,
         data.table,
         microbenchmark,
         testthat (>= 2.1.0)
